00:04:58.399 --> 00:05:03.399
Now it's really helping the student to connect the dots, so to speak.

00:05:03.399 --> 00:05:09.399
See how the material applies to decisions that they're making in their life.

00:05:09.399 --> 00:05:16.399
Throughout the Bible study, we want to constantly direct attention to Jehovah God.

00:05:16.399 --> 00:05:21.399
And if we're talking too much as the teacher, it's going to be hard to accomplish that.

00:05:21.399 --> 00:05:34.399
Your effective use of questions can help them connect their Bible knowledge that they're receiving to the qualities of Jehovah God that's going to make them love him.

00:05:34.399 --> 00:05:40.399
This is such as his love, his goodness, and his righteousness.

00:05:40.399 --> 00:05:45.399
Here's an example of a question that might be used.

00:05:45.399 --> 00:05:51.399
Why do you think Jehovah would forbid a certain action?

00:05:51.399 --> 00:05:59.399
See, that kind of question is helping your student begin to understand the thinking of Jehovah God on matters.

00:05:59.399 --> 00:06:03.399
Did you notice it was not a yes or no question?

00:06:03.399 --> 00:06:07.399
The question actually started with why.

00:06:07.399 --> 00:06:17.399
And now that forces the student to go to another level of their thought process to explain the reason Jehovah forbids certain actions.

00:06:17.399 --> 00:06:23.399
And that's a very good method of reaching the heart of a student.

00:06:23.399 --> 00:06:26.399
Here's an example of another question.

00:06:26.399 --> 00:06:31.399
